Philip Thresher (1 March 1844 – 11 April 1883) was an English first-class cricketer.
Thresher made his first-class debut for Hampshire in 1865 against Surrey. This was Thresher's only match in 1865.
Thresher played two matches against in the 1866 season against the Marylebone Cricket Club and Surrey.
Thresher's next first-class appearance for Hampshire came in the 1869 season with two matches against the Marylebone Cricket Club.
Thresher died at Shepherd's Bush, London on 11 April 1883.
